<p><b>Mahayana sutras</b> are a very broad genre of <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhist</a> scriptures of which the <a href="/wiki/Mahayana" title="Mahayana">Mahayana</a> Buddhist tradition claim that they are original teachings of the <a href="/wiki/Gautama_Buddha" title="Gautama Buddha">Buddha</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Theravada" title="Theravada">Theravada</a> and the other <a href="/wiki/Early_Buddhist_Schools" title="Early Buddhist Schools" class="mw-redirect">Early Buddhist Schools</a> claim that the Mahayana Sutras are later compositions, not taught by the Buddha.</p>
